sp.p:
Then you say as I say;
for, I am
sure, he is not Hector.

So let it now;
for it has been a great
while going by.

Well, cousin,
I told you a thing yesterday;
think on't.

Then would come some matter from
him;
I see none now.

But yet you look not well upon him;
for whosoever
you take him to be, he is Ajax.

You depend upon a noble gentleman;
I must
needs praise him.

Fears make devils of cherubins;
they never see
truly.

Let me bear another to his horse;
for that's the
more capable creature.

No, no, I am a rascal; a scurvy
railing knave;
a very filthy rogue.
